adjectives.description: unsuspicious (comparative more unsuspicious, superlative most unsuspicious)

entries.meaning: Not suspicious; not suspecting, unaware (of something).

examples: The skeletons in this sport’s hitherto unsuspicious closet belong to upward of a dozen top-notch show jumpers, all insured for $50,000 to $250,000, all killed by a hitman-for-hire in an insurance-fraud scheme perpetrated by some of the most sterling names in the business.
